reviewText: Love John Wayne, and The Big Trail is his earliest film - and is hard to find!
Received in time stated very satisfied with purchase.
As a big fan of all landscapes Southwest USA, this movie provides great vistas. The story is a JW story, not the best, not the worst. Great to have around in the library when it's snowing outside.

i liked camancheros but the BT was too dated. most of john waynes films form the late 50's, 60's and 70's still holdup for me. i really enjoy them and purchased every one of them on DVD. this is a good by for Comancheros is very good and unlike me you may like the Big Trail. and see Big Jake and Chisum 2 to add to your collection.
